VI. MATERIALS AND METHODS
Simulations were done with both an iterative, numerically exact diagonalization of the master equation as well as Gillespie simulations [60]. In both, we employ a separation of timescales for electron transfer to or from a transistor and gate charging, afforded by the large gate capacitance. Specifically, the large capacitance means we can update Vg with discrete time step, chosen to be 10βh¯, and compute rates at ﬁxed Vg in-between these dynamical updates. More details on the models and calculations can be found in Appendices A and D.
